Source: pg-sorted-heap
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), gcc
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/skuznetsov/pg_sorted_heap

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-sorted-heap
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-sorted-heap
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: sorted heap table access method for PostgreSQL PGVERSION
  pg_sorted_heap physically sorts PostgreSQL table storage by primary key,
  prunes heap blocks with per-page zone maps, and includes built-in vector
  types plus planner-integrated HNSW search.
